Summary: Major changes to useability of reference policy
Keywords: 

Rewrote the policy postinst in perl to allow us to do module dependency
checks, and to map policy modules to debian packages, in order to better
detect the modules that would be necessary for the target machine.  This
is a common postinst for all policy packages we build.

Also, compiling with either MCS or MLS produced errors while installing
policy, since we lack setrans daemon. So we are now building with out
them, created an easy to modify option to re-enable it later.

Updated modules.conf to use the latest offerings from Erich.
